  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "LN3qb7DB8t2x1PcW9ktNJ/VUTMc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Decision (2026-04-18)\n\nThe typing-indicator UI (formerly \"Track A\") is **not shipping**.\n\n## Rationale\n\nPSS message latency is 2-10 seconds because of Trojan chunk mining and push-sync. A \"User is typing...\" hint doesn't pay off when the message itself arrives on a longer timescale than the hint would cover. The signal would flicker or misfire more often than it would help.\n\n## Scope of the decision\n\n- **No UI indicator** for typing in chat.\n- **Presence dots** (green-dot + \"Last seen ...\") are **parked**, not deleted. Low payoff relative to live collaboration, which is what users actually want next.\n- **Adapter hooks stay.** `sendTyping`, `sendStoppedTyping`, `sendPresence`, `onNotification` remain in the GSOC notifier because they are useful primitives for presence and live collab.\n\n## Consequence\n\nEngineering attention redirects from ephemeral status indicators toward the live-collaboration track, where the latency profile is tolerable and the payoff is concrete.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z"
    }
  },
